pr_review_comment_body:
I honestly think the `try...except` block is a bit more clear here, and it avoids any edge cases with determining what is and isn't a float. If Python thinks it's a float, why argue with it?

You may want to try to coerce this to a `Decimal` though, that way you don't need to worry about floating point oddities.

```python
try:
    return decimal.Decimal(string)
except decimal.DecimalException:
    return False
```

If you want to be _really careful_, there are [other edge cases](https://github.com/tomchristie/django-rest-framework/blob/ff0eeaf77addc29d1ce0c10f47948ad06611f526/rest_framework/fields.py#L924-L936) that we handle in DRF for parsing decimal values.

So this will add the `pipe` method to the deferred, but not to the promise - using `.then` or `.promise` would yield a promise that does not have a `pipe` method unless I'm mistaken.

In order to get the method available everywhere it needs to be, this probably needs to look like

```js
function pipe() { ... }

deferred.pipe = deferred.promise().pipe = pipe;
```

@AbdealiJK Fair point...
The solution could be to have two functions then: `rgba2rgba` :grimacing:  with the complete functionality and `rgba2rgb` which calls the former under the hood.
Should ask for more opinions on this though.

